<Objects>
  <!-- Ordinary Client - ANUBI'S LAIR (Hard dungeon; gold sandstone Egyptian temple).
       Recovered from video footage (build_ledger.json, 2x-confirmed taunts):
       Anubis (Egyptian death-god) is INVULNERABLE and calls on his PILLARS for protection
       ("Pillars... please help me!"); destroy the 4 Pillars to break the ward, then he
       weakens ("I am losing strength... I am slowly dying...") and becomes killable.
       PILLARS mechanic is a drop-in on the Gate-to-the-Underworld/Ra-and-Staves pattern.
       TAUNTS are verbatim-recovered; attack PATTERNS are reconstructed (no fight-frame data).
       Placeholder sprites (chars16x16dEncounters2); reused projectiles. ids 0x8f00-0x8f01 + portal 0x8213. -->
  <Object type="0x8f00" id="Anubis">
    <Group>Anubi's Lair</Group>
